      {
        "id": "994abc4947089416f47fe94b399b3b7f87592fb7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-15 13:29:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "78754a253c714c97a0ae179a70987aadc1e8260a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-15 14:22:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nThis code doesn't seem to be working like that, only checks for \"abbrev\" and discards what was passed in.   \n\nIn any case, I would assume query parameters should be fairly limited in its usage, and should be specified in the XacmlPdpRestController in the swagger apidoc to show up it generated UIs.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f9dd5fa085bd23ce4bdcf151d7b7351eee1d1cdd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1757,
          "name": "Ali Hockla",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ah999m@att.com",
          "username": "ah999m"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-15 14:44:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > (1 comment)\n> \n> This code doesn't seem to be working like that, only checks for \"abbrev\" and discards what was passed in.   \n> \n> In any case, I would assume query parameters should be fairly limited in its usage, and should be specified in the XacmlPdpRestController in the swagger apidoc to show up it generated UIs.\n\n\"abbrev\" is currently the only additional parameter that is accepted and supported. The idea was that if/when another requirement is introduced for another parameter then the DecisionProvider can be modified to handle and pass it along accordingly",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "957eed518077f0e75a2e48b824738f706e107440",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1757,
          "name": "Ali Hockla",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ah999m@att.com",
          "username": "ah999m"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-15 14:45:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > > (1 comment)\n> > \n> > This code doesn't seem to be working like that, only checks for \"abbrev\" and discards what was passed in.   \n> > \n> > In any case, I would assume query parameters should be fairly limited in its usage, and should be specified in the XacmlPdpRestController in the swagger apidoc to show up it generated UIs.\n> \n> \"abbrev\" is currently the only additional parameter that is accepted and supported. The idea was that if/when another requirement is introduced for another parameter then the DecisionProvider can be modified to handle and pass it along accordingly\n\nMy next task is to update the swagger api doc, I'm currently working on that",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
